items.title: BMW posts 37% drop in annual net profit, warns of 'subdued' Chinese demand
items.description: BMW's net profits slumped by more than a third in 2024 as weaker demand in China and Germany weighed on the high-end car manufacturer.

items.title: Ulta issues weak guidance, citing consumer uncertainty, rising competition and company missteps
items.description: Ulta Beauty warned that profits and revenue will be worse than Wall Street expected in the year ahead.

items.title: Adobe shares drop 14% as concerns about AI growth overshadow better-than-expected results
items.description: Adobe shares fell on Thursday as investors fretted over lingering growth concerns and the company's artificial intelligence monetization strategy.

items.title: American Eagle says consumer is slowing down, issues weak guidance
